A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Chapter 4 of Title 1 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
2 holidays and observances, so as to designate the fourth Friday in November of each year as
3 "National Sugarcane Syrup Day" in Georgia; to provide legislative findings and declarations;
4 to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
6 SECTION 1.
7 The General Assembly finds that:
8 (1) Making sugarcane syrup has been a part of family farm tradition for generations,
9 particularly in Georgia;
10 (2) The increase in production costs, competition from artificial syrups, and the decreasing
11 number of farmers who still make sugarcane syrup, however, has led some to refer to the
12 making of sugarcane syrup as a dying art;
13 (3) Establishing a "National Sugarcane Syrup Day" in Georgia would help to preserve the
14 art of making sugarcane syrup by honoring those who continue with this long-standing
15 family farm tradition and by raising public awareness of the differences between natural
16 sugarcane syrup and artificial syrups;
