17 (4) Designating the fourth Friday in November of each year, the day after Thanksgiving,
18 as "National Sugarcane Syrup Day" is particularly fitting, as it is not only a time when
19 families gather and celebrate together, but also a time when some say sugarcane is at its
20 sweetest in Georgia; and
21 (5) It is, therefore, abundantly fitting and proper that the State of Georgia appropriately
22 recognize and honor the family farm tradition of making sugarcane syrup by designating
23 the fourth Friday in November of each year as "National Sugarcane Syrup Day" in Georgia.
24 SECTION 2.
25 Chapter 4 of Title 1 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to holidays and
26 observances, is amended by adding a new Code section to read as follows:
27 "1-4-27.
28 The fourth Friday in November of each year is designated as 'National Sugarcane Syrup
29 Day' in Georgia."
30 SECTION 3.
31 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
